label: L.I.E.S.
description:
L.I.E.S. capo Morelli allows for more classic club emotion in his raw disco-house buckers on the label’s 200th release - RIYL Traxx, Daft Punk, Adonis, Legowelt.

‘Heart Stopper’ was recorded 2019-2022 and bears strong traces of Morelli’s tenure in Paris manifest in its french touch filter-house nudges and kinky gallic gait, which finely balances the album’s more scowling industrial parts, made with a relatively heart-on-sleeve style of melodic sequencing, vocal parts and craftier rhythm... more

label: Disciples
description:
Dazzlingly diverse material that locks in to Wolf Eyes' history of untethered collaboration, with a handpicked selection of belters from the long-running noise troupe's recent box of private-press 7"s. Features Aaron Dilloway, Raven Chacon, Gretchen Gonzales, Alex Moskos, and core duo Nate Young and John Olson, going full gnarr in the best way.

It's tuff to know what to expect of Wolf Eyes in 2023 and that's probably for the best. The band has been through so many personnel shifts over its... more

title_full:
MUN SING

              —
              Inflatable Gravestone
            
              (Planet Mu Records Ltd.)
label: Planet Mu Records Ltd.
description:
Giant Swan's Harry Wright grapples with loss on their debut solo album, following impressive EPs for Infinite Machine and SVBKVLT with a set of tightly engineered, pneumatic club tracks and surreal pop deconstructions. RIYL Rian Treanor, SOPHIE, Lee Gamble.

When Wright lost their father suddenly in 2020, they channeled their grief into their work, attempting to mirror the process they were experiencing. This explains the album's blackly comic title, that makes light work of an emotional... more

label: Voam
description:
Blawan & Pariah pull back to proper meat motor techno as Karenn

The first new Karenn sesh since 2020’s ‘Music Sounds Better With Shoe’ lands with the dance packed again, delivering four propulsive screwballs marked by weirdo production tics and vocals.

label: Downwards
description:
Original goth, Annie Hogan presents an extraordinary regression session of astral planing organs, keys and submerged field recordings on a new album for her pals at Downwards, reminding us of everything from Mihály Víg’s ‘Bela Tarr’ score to Sun Ra jams, Nate Young’s gunk to Pauline Oliveros’s deep listening works.

From her seaside perch, Studio Blue in The Wirral, she supplies a wholly absorbing hour of layered and mulched organ and field recordings that pushes the aesthetic of her... more

label: XL Recordings
description:
Blawan’s first solo EP in 2 years is a straight winner for fans of gunky modular freakiness and experimental electronics, introducing his new vocal spar Monstera Black.

‘Dismantled into Juice’ is also his 2nd for XL after the watershed moment of ‘Woke Up Right Handed’, where his typically unruly techno style went totally off course into non-standard meters and chewy textures with wild abandon.
